description: THE KENTS recounts Superman's adopted family's settlement in Kansas in the 1860s. Told against the backdrop of the Civil War and the western expansion movement, this book tells the epic tale of Nathaniel and Jebediah Kent, two brothers divided by personal and political differences. Featuring cameos by some of the most popular figures of the time including Wild Bill Hickok, Buffalo Bill Cody, Jesse James and George Custer, this volume is an excellent representation of the issues and events of that turbulent era.
name: TPB

description: It is well known that the demise of the super group StormWatch led to the birth of their successors, the Authority. But until now the inner origins of how the most powerful team in the WildStorm Universe came together has never been revealed. Seen through the eyes of Jenny Sparks, "The Spirit of the Twentieth Century" and Authority team leader, we experience Jenny's first meetings with all of her teammates and learn how each encounter took place during pivotal points in Twentieth century history. From stealing mystical artifacts from the Nazis to working with government covert op teams during the '80s, the true beginnings of the Authority are finally told.
name: TPB

volume.name: Jenny Sparks: The Secret History of the Authority

description:
A perfect companion to CRISIS ON INFINITE EARTHS, this trade paperback is a definitive history of the DC Universe based on the consequences of that epic tale. Narrated by Harbinger, a central figure in the Crisis storyline, the reader is brought through the new history of the world and its heroes. Featuring virtually every character in the DC Universe, including Batman, Superman, Wonder Woman, Aquaman, Green Lantern, and the Flash, this tale takes us from the dawn of creation to the end of recorded history and lays the foundation for adventures to come.

Notes:

Reprints of History of the DC Universe #1 and History of the DC Universe #2.
name: TPB

volume.name: The History of the DC Universe

description:
Collecting the high-octane 5-issue miniseries! In their prime, Able "Speed" Monroe and Ichabod McQueen were couriers capable of ferrying anything, anywhere, anytime. Now almost obsolete, they're called out of retirement to deliver some very dangerous cargo for a dead President. If only they knew what is was â€” and why everyone else wants to kill them for it.

Back Blurb

TWO MEN. ONE SHOOTS. ONE DRIVES.

Each the best at what they do. And each old enough to collect Social Security. Couriers extraordinaire: The Highwaymen.

Now, Able Monroe and Mr. McQueen are pulled out of retirement to execute one last mission for a late president of the United States of America. A young girl named Grace Anderson must be escorted to the Centers for Disease Control as fast as humanly possible. Why? Because she just might be the most insidious weapon of mass destruction ever created by the US government. And a twisted member of that government wants to use her to devastate a major American city.

From writers Marc Bernandin and Adam Freeman (Monster Attack Network), and artist Lee Garbett (MIDNIGHTER) comes this critically-acclaimed thrill ride about men in the sunset of their lives who remember what it was like to be heroes.
name: TPB

description: An all-out, pedal-to-the-metal action tale in the Cliffhanger tradition! Collecting the 6-issue HIGH ROADS miniseries, this volume tells the story of a mismatched group of ne'er-do-wells and misfits who find themselves involved in a treasure hunt of most improbable proportions.
name: TPB

description: Giselle is captured by the revolution and must find a way out and back to the palace before Verne's moons fall out of alignment. Can Genevieve, burned by Giselle's betrayal, find it in her heart to believe her?
name: Maximum Darkness

description: One of the most fondly remembered characters from the British comics of the 1950s returns in a tensely told and lushly rendered tale of honor, duty, loyalty and sacrifice. This volume collects the acclaimed 5-issue miniseries written by Garth Ennis (PREACHER).
name: TPB

description: The greatest heroes from two publishers â€” DC Comics and Top Cow â€” meet for the first time and face off against each other and their greatest foes in this staggering collection! This volume features the best-selling crossovers THE DARKNESS/BATMAN, THE DARKNESS/SUPERMAN #1-2, JLA/CYBERFORCE and JLA/WITCHBLADE.
name: TPB

description: While on a top-secret mission as part of an elite Cold War black ops team, Navy Seal Michael Cray was betrayed and exposed to a hazardous mutagen. Twenty years later with the exposure finally manifesting itself, the world's deadliest mercenary suddenly became a living weapon with extraordinary powers. Changing his ways and taking on the guise of Deathblow, Cray now looks to save his soul by becoming mankind's last hope of survival in an epic battle between good and evil. Standing alone against the Dark Angel and his four horsemen, Deathblow must find a way to protect the Holy Grail and the child of Light or bear witness to Armageddon.
name: TPB

description: Collecting issues #1-9 of the acclaimed series written by Brian Azzarello (100 BULLETS)! Michael Cray â€” codename: Deathblow â€” is perhaps the deadliest man in the world, long thought dead. And when it's revealed that he's been alive for years, things get complicated. But not as complicated as when a talking dog, a psychotic dinosaur robot and weaponized rats join the fray.
name: And Then You Live!

description: Collecting 2010's five unforgettable one-shots that took a modern look at warfare courtesy of some of today's top comic talents. Includes G.I. COMBAT #1 featuring The Haunted Tank, OUR ARMY AT WAR #1 starring Sgt. Rock, WEIRD WAR TALES #1, OUR FIGHTING FORCES #1 spotlighting The Losers, and STAR-SPANGLED WAR STORIES #1 focusing on French Resistance icon Mademoiselle Marie!
name: TPB

description:
The 10th Muse is back in this all-new story featuring her nemesis Medusa!

This action packed story will be the pre-cursor to Bluewater's new ongoing 10th Muse series.

Collecting the beautifully illustrated 6-issue miniseries! In Tokyo, A.D. 2063, Renjiro is caught between a lifetime of loyalty to his Yakuza clan and the iron-fisted might of the military elite, and he will soon learn that the only way to avoid total annihilation is to play both sides against the middle.
name: TPB

description: A volume reprinting STORMWATCH: TEAM ACHILLES #1-6 plus the preview from Wizard! Created and funded by the United Nations, StormWatch: Team Achilles is a group of highly trained human operatives with one mission: to police the world's growing super-human population!
name: Volume 1

description: Collecting issues #7-11 of the acclaimed series - five short stories that spotlight the members of Team Achilles. Created and funded by the United Nations, Stormwatch: Team Achilles is a group of highly trained human operatives armed with the latest weaponry and gadgets and given a mission: to police the world's growing superhuman population. Led by former Black Razor, Ben Santini and featuring an international cast, these are gritty stories of hard-edged, military fiction with political undertones.
name: Volume 2

description:
Fortune favours the boldâ€¦

They were an unstoppable force, hired to take the crown from the King of Persia. They were a fearless army of Greek soldiers, and one hundred thousand men fighting as one. They were led by the finest and most courageous generals in all of Greece. They were being led to unimaginable wealth, but that was days ago.

Now their leaders are dead and their army has scattered. Now their numbers have fallen to ten thousand and nothing remains but fear. Now they are men praying not for victory, but for the slim chance of living one more day.

Cut off by impassable terrain and pursued by an army of one million enemy soldiers; they must stand together to survive. To find their way home, one of their own must lead them. And to live one more day...

...they must fight.

Written by Lewis Helfand with art by Lalit Kumar Singh.

Softcover, 72 pages, full color.

volume.name: 400 BC: The Story of the Ten Thousand

name: Warrior of the Law

description:
Doctor Who Magazine 441 asks MARCUS WILSON to give us a peek under the Christmas tree to see whatâ€™s waiting to be unwrapped on Christmas Day, in an exclusive, in-depth interview with Doctor Whoâ€™s producerâ€¦

â€œItâ€™s Christmas turned up to 12. Itâ€™s the most Christmassy Christmas Special weâ€™ve ever seen. Itâ€™s a lovely, heart-warming, touching tale. Itâ€™s literally magical. Itâ€™s full of the usual concoction of things that spew out of Stevenâ€™s imagination. Youâ€™re going, â€˜How can you have that and that in the same story?â€™ â€“ and yet it worksâ€¦â€

ALSO THIS ISSUE:

HOLDING THE BABY
DWM talks to CLOSING TIME director, STEVE HUGHES, who reveals the secrets of turning a department store into a haunted house, giving the Cybermats teeth, and defending the honour of Adric!

LIKE FATHER, LIKE SON
DWM goes behind the scenes of SERPENT CREST, AudioGOâ€™s latest series of audio dramas featuring Tom Baker as the Fourth Doctor, and talks exclusively to DAVID TROUGHTON â€“ who joins the cast to take on his fatherâ€™s role as the Second Doctor!

HEREâ€™S TO THE FUTURE! Executive producer Steven Moffat writes about experiencing Christmas in the snow, his plans for Doctor Who in 2012, and the seriesâ€™ 50th anniversary, in PRODUCTION NOTES!

SCHOOL WINNERS!
DWM joins the crew of DOCTOR WHO CONFIDENTIAL and visits the pupils of Oakley Junior School to meet MATT SMITH and watch their winning entry for the â€˜Script to Screenâ€™ competition, DEATH IS THE ONLY ANSWER â€“ featuring Albert Einstein and an Ood!

AND THE WINNERS AREâ€¦ The results of the DWM merchandise poll for the most popular books, audios, and DVDs of 2010 are revealed at last â€“ along with your views on DWM itself!

SHOCK RETURN THE FACT OF FICTION is filled with fascinating facts and sinister Cybermen, as it focuses its attention on the much-loved Fifth Doctor adventure from 1982, EARTHSHOCK!

LETâ€™S HAVE A PARTYâ€¦ OR NOT? As the 50th anniversary of DOCTOR WHO approaches in 2013, how best to mark the occasion â€“ celebrate the past with a multi-Doctor extravaganza or pave the way to the future with something new, original and completely unexpected? Thereâ€™s only one way to decideâ€¦ get debating duo TOBY HADOKE and JOHNNY CANDON to argue the toss in A BATTLE OF WITS!

THE CHILD OF TIME The Doctor, Amy and Alan Turing face their ultimate encounter with the time-twisting Chiyoko in the thrilling climax to the Eleventh Doctorâ€™s latest comic-strip adventure, THE CHILD OF TIME by JONATHAN MORRIS with art by MARTIN GERAGHTY!

GOING FOURTH Itâ€™s the season that saw the return of the Daleks, the Cybermen and the Sontaransâ€¦ and the very first appearance of Davros! Discover more as DWMâ€™s COUNTDOWN TO 50 looks back at 1974/5â€™s Series Twelve and the dÃ©but of Tom Baker as the Fourth Doctor.

ITâ€™S ALL BEEN FANTASTIC! The Time Team shed a tear as they reach the end of the Ninth Doctor era with THE PARTING OF THE WAYS â€“ what will Emma, Michael, Chris and Will make of the Time Lordâ€™s encounter with the Dalek Emperor and the Bad Wolf?

PLUS! All the latest official news, TV and merchandise reviews, previews, competitions, a prize-winning crossword and much, much more!
name: Celebrate Christmas with the Doctor!

description: Chapter Three
name: Chapter Three

description:
Captain America has fallen into a clash with his government and his friends, and the people close to him are paying the price. The life of Cap's girlfriend, Sharon Carter, is torn apart as her superiors use her divided loyalties against her. Elsewhere, a new villain emerges; the Red Skull begins to make himself known; and the Winter Soldier again comes face-to-face with Cap. But which side will he choose?

Plus: James Buchanan Barnes, Captain America's one-time partner Bucky, faces his first Christmas of the 21st century - and the truth of the terrible things he was forced to do as the Winter Soldier. And with Cap caught in a conflict he can neither take a side of - or understand - what moves can he make to try to redeem himself?!
name: TPB

description: SPIDER-ISLAND AFTERMATH Flash Thompson suffered a great loss during the Infestation, but in the wake of the outbreak, the body count may rise. The dust has settled, the outbreak is over, but the heartbreak has just begun.
name: Capital Punishment

description: Collecting Deadpool MAX volume 1 #1-3.

volume.name: Deadpool MAX: A History of Violence

description: In this issue, a member of X-Factor dies.

GUEST STARRING IRON MAN 2.0! The fallout of Schism pushes the X-Men and War Machine at each other in Eastern Europe as sentinels are being traded on the black market. But things arenâ€™t as they seem and the X-Men and War Machine are going to have to work together to stop a truly horrible plot.
The bloodbath continues. No one is safe.
Andrea still mourns for Dale.
name: A Larger World

description: The strongest man in the universe is rampaging on the surface of Panoptes, and the Dominators are massing in the skies above â€“ and naturally, The Legion is stuck between the two! They don't have the raw power to stare down either threat â€“ but what they do have is a planâ€¦one that puts some of their own in even greater danger behind enemy lines!
name: Shadow War

description:
Ever since he died and became Deadman, Boston Brand has served the deity known as Rama Kushna, inhabiting bodies to complete missions that she dictates. Now, for the first time, Deadman may have a clue how he can gain some control over his "life." But the cost may be the souls of the bodies he inhabits!

*James Gordon makes a background cameo
name: Twenty Questions, Part 3

description: Continuing his story from back-up in Ariboy, Skywolf and the Bald Eagle go on a treasure hunt in Viet Nam.
name: The War Garden

description: As Bruce digs deeper into the mystery of the recent owl murders, he soon finds himself face to face with a shocking enemy â€“ an enemy the Wayne family has secretly been at war with for centuries. Be there for the first shots of the war for the soul of Gotham City. Friends will become deadly enemies and secrets will be revealed â€“ revelations that will change the Bat-family forever.
name: The Thirteenth Hour

description: The Big Top comes to the Windy City! After the massive events of issue 2, the circus heads to Chicago â€“ and Dick Grayson is along for the ride! But as Nightwing puts pressure on ex-Haley connections in search for answers about his past, one lead may be far too explosive to handle! Be here as Nightwing takes his quest for the truth to the Second City!
name: Past and Present

description: Someone's come up with a way to turn ordinary citizens of Gotham City into undetectable walking bombsâ€¦and only Black Canary (a.k.a. Dinah Laurel Lance), Starling (a.k.a. Ev Crawford) and new team member Katana (a.k.a. Tatsu Yamashiro) can stop them. But will Canary's choice of a fourth team member, a notorious bioterrorist, tear them apart first?
name: You Might Think

description: Cats hate baths. Cats hate dogs. And cats hate being caught. Catwoman stole from the wrong man, and now he's got her. He wants his stuff back, he wants answers and he wants blood. Cats had better have nine lives, because Selina Kyle is about to lose one!
name: No One Can Find Any Piece Of Me Here

description: Across the country, bodies litter the streets as the Queen of Blood builds her army. A weakened Andrew must seek the aid of an old ally, but the game of death has a new wild card who may help Andrew tip the balance of power â€“ or decapitate him.
name: Numb

description: Hippolyta, the queen of the Amazons, has kept a secret from her daughter all her life â€“ and when it's revealed, Wonder Woman's life will shatter like brittle clay. The only one more shocked than Diana by this revelation? Bloodthirsty Hera herself â€“ so why is her sinister daughter, Strife, so eager for the truth to be told?
name: Clay

description:
Newly bonded with his alien armor, high-schooler Jaime Reyes must keep his symbiotic partner from enacting its mission: to conquer planet Earth. Can a teenager turn an alien weapon of mass destruction into a force for good?

Jaime Reyes fights with Khaji da just to allow him to be seen out from under the exoskeleton that surrounds him. La Dama is furious about her henchmen failing kills Coyote to locate the Jaime with a magic spell. Reach and Khaji Kai is closing in on the newly activate Khaji Da. Lastly, the Brotherhood of Evil is sent back in action with Silverback.
name: Metamorphosis, Conclusion

description:
Captain Atom is taking his powers to new heights â€“ saving people all across the world in the blink of an eye. But he's not the only one who can move at super speed. Enter: The Flash! And when their paths cross, don't expect them to share the secret hero's handshake â€“ because Captain Atom may be a bigger threat than any villain.

Captain Atom displays near god-like power saving people all over the United States. He even goes to a battle in Libya where he run into Flash (Barry Allan) who (surprise, surprise) is not a fan. Captain Atom then goes back to the Continuum and runs into General Eiling.
name: Divine Intervention

description:
Things go from bad to worse as Guy Gardner and John Stewart's squad of Green Lanterns is vastly outnumbered by the Intruders, a force that knows how to neutralize any green ring's power. And these invaders have made it abundantly clear: this is personal.

The Seven Green Lanterns locate the ones who have been killing Lanterns and go to bring them to justice only to be overwhelmed by the shear number of the opposition. The Lanterns need to be evacuated or reinforcements quick. They manage to get to the seven but ended up leaving seven behind including John Stewart.
name: Force of Will
